import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}><MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"snapshot"}}>{`snapshot`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Snapshot the current version of the factory's working directory.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"options"}}>{`Options`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}><MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`-m`}</MDXTag>{`, `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`--message`}</MDXTag>{`: a message describing the snapshot. Default: `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`n/a`}</MDXTag></MDXTag></MDXTag>
